This paper deals with information theory and communication networks, which are typically categorized under cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the method of types, which is a common tool in information theory and is often used in cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) research. The paper's focus on strong converse theorems and reliability functions suggests that it may also be relevant to cs.SY (Systems and Control) research. Finally, the paper specifically mentions relay channels, which are a common topic in cs.MM (Multimedia).
